<a name="san-jacinto"></a> 
<div class="problem-heading reset-counter">Removal of the San Jacinto on-ramp will eliminate freeway access for a large area</div>

<div class="textblock">

    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>The plan entirely removes the San Jacinto on-ramp</li>
        <li>The San Jacinto on-ramp provides freeway access for a very large area, including south Midtown, the Museum District, the Richmond corridor extending west of Montrose, and Medical Center traffic coming north on San Jacinto.</li>
                <li>Removal of the ramp will force all this traffic to use much longer and much more inconvenient routes to get on the freeway system, which will mean going to the South Freeway (SH 288) for most people. Reaching I-45 will be especially long
                    and cumbersome.</li>

    </ul>

    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Do not remove this ramp</li>
        <li>If closure is deemed to be necessary during the peak traffic periods, close it only during the peak period but leave it open at all other times.</li>

    </ul>

</div>

