<a name="two-way-hov-outside-loop"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">There is no need for a two-way HOV lane facility outside the loop</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div class="problem-solution">Two-way HOV is not needed outside the loop</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Outside the loop, traffic in the off-peak direction almost always moves at posted speeds</li>
        <li>A two-way HOV will possibly violate design standards and have complications at the T-ramp to the Westpark transit center</li>
                <li>A two-way HOV would need to be transitioned to a one-way HOV outside the Beltway</li>

    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Do not convert the HOV lane to two-way operation outside the loop.</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="#top">Back to top</a>
</div>




<a name="two-way-hov-inside-loop""></a>
<div class="problem-heading">A two-way HOV facility inside the loop should start around Buffalo Speedway and go eastward to avoid major complexities</div>
<div class="textblock">
    <div>A two-way HOV inside the Loop would be beneficial in the inbound direction in the afternoon, when there is typically a long backup from SH 288 interchange to around Kirby.</div>
    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Bringing a two-way HOV facility through the Loop 610 interchange and through the Edloe connections will be difficult and costly, and the <a href="http://www.mysouthwestfreeway.com/docs/2015-09-28-US59-Rider42-Final-Report-DRAFT.pdf">report</a> expects new elevated structures to be needed</li>
        <li>The two-way HOV is not needed west of Buffalo Speedway</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>If a two-way HOV is deemed to be desirable inside the loop, it should exist from around Buffalo Speedway to around Mandell only. West of Buffalo Speedway it should stay as-is, a one-way reversible facility</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="#top">Back to top</a>
</div>


<br />

<a name="hov-entrance"></a>
<div class="problem-heading">Adding a northbound entrance to the HOV lane between Bellaire and Hillcroft will worsen the traffic slowdowns in that area</div>
<div class="textblock">

    <div class="problem-solution">Problem</div>
    <ul>
        <li>In the morning on Monday through Thursday, the inbound HOV traffic slows down and often reaches a stop between Bellaire and Hillcroft. The HOV is already over capacity in this area.</li>
        <li>Adding an entrance ramp to the over-capacity HOV will make congestion on the HOV even worse.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="problem-solution">Potential Solution</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Do not add the entrance to the HOV. </li>
                <li>If an entrance is added, have a long transition zone to prevent backups onto the freeway main lanes</li>

    </ul>
</div>

